    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Exercices Semaine 10\"\nformat:\n  html:\n    html-math-method: mathjax\n    include-after-body: include/webex_2.js\n    css: include/webex_2.css\ntoc: false\neditor: source\n---\n\n\n\n\n\n<!-- JavaScript for legacy hint/explanation buttons -->\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\nfunction toggleAlertLegacy(alertId, message, type) {\n  var alertBox = document.getElementById(alertId);\n  if (!alertBox) return;\n\n  var alertsContainer = alertBox.closest('.question-alerts');\n  if (alertsContainer) {\n    var allAlerts = alertsContainer.querySelectorAll('.alert');\n    allAlerts.forEach(function(alert) {\n      if (alert.id !== alertId) {\n        alert.style.display = \"none\";\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  var alertMessage = alertBox.querySelector(\".alertMessage\");\n  var alertType = alertBox.querySelector(\".alertType\");\n\n  if (alertBox.style.display === \"block\") {\n    alertBox.style.display = \"none\";\n  } else {\n    alertMessage.innerHTML = message;\n    alertType.innerHTML = (type === 'hint') ? '&#10067; Indice' : '&#128161; Explication';\n\n    var isDark = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark';\n    alertBox.style.backgroundColor = (type === 'hint')\n      ? (isDark ? '#3a3520' : '#FFEDA3')\n      : (isDark ? '#1a3a2a' : '#C0EDC2');\n    alertBox.style.borderColor = (type === 'hint')\n      ? (isDark ? '#d69e2e' : '#E5B800')\n      : (isDark ? '#68d391' : '#388E3C');\n    alertBox.style.color = isDark ? '#e2e8f0' : '#1a202c';\n    alertBox.style.display = \"block\";\n\n    MathJax.typesetPromise([alertMessage]);\n  }\n}\n</script>\n\n<!-- CSS for AI Help button and alerts container -->\n<style>\n.custom-button.ai-help {\n  background: #E8E0F0;\n  border: 2px solid #5a3d8a;\n}\n\n.custom-button.ai-help:hover {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5a67d8 0%, #9f7aea 100%);\n  border-color: transparent;\n  color: white;\n  transform: scale(1.05);\n}\n\n[data-theme=\"dark\"] .custom-button.ai-help {\n  background: #2d2440;\n  border-color: #7c6aad;\n  color: #e2e8f0;\n}\n\n[data-theme=\"dark\"] .custom-button.ai-help:hover {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5a67d8 0%, #9f7aea 100%);\n  border-color: transparent;\n  color: white;\n}\n\n.question-alerts {\n  margin-top: 8px;\n}\n\n.question-alerts .alert {\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n}\n</style>\n\n<!-- MathJax for Rendering Math -->\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" async\n  src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/3.2.2/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n</script>\n\n\n---\n\n## Question 1\n\nDans une étude sur l'opinion publique concernant un traité international, un échantillon aléatoire de \\\\(200\\\\) personnes a été interrogé. Parmi ces personnes, \\\\(120\\\\) ont déclaré être en faveur du traité. Quelle est la proportion estimée de personnes favorables au traité dénotée \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\)?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_VGMRFCLJDZ'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VGMRFCLJDZ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.50\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VGMRFCLJDZ\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.60\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VGMRFCLJDZ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.70\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VGMRFCLJDZ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.80\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q1-hint', 'Utilisez la formule de l\\'estimateur d\\'une proportion : \\\\(\\\\hat{p} = \\\\frac{m}{n}\\\\), où \\\\(m\\\\) est le nombre de personnes favorables et \\\\(n\\\\) est la taille de l\\'échantillon.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q1-expl', 'L\\'estimateur \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) est calculé comme suit : \\\\(\\\\hat{p} = \\\\frac{120}{200} = 0.60\\\\). Donc, la proportion estimée de personnes favorables au traité est \\\\(0.60\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q1-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q1-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 2\n\nEn considérant le même contexte que la question \\\\(1\\\\), quelle est l'erreur standard de la proportion estimée \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_CEEDBKDEIN'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_CEEDBKDEIN\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\( \\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p}) \\\\approx  0.0346\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_CEEDBKDEIN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p}) \\\\approx 0.0462\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_CEEDBKDEIN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p}) \\\\approx 0.513\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_CEEDBKDEIN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p}) \\\\approx 0.0264\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q2-hint', 'Utilisez la formule de l\\'erreur standard pour une proportion : \\\\(\\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{\\\\hat{p}(1-\\\\hat{p})}{n}}\\\\), où \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) est la proportion estimée et \\\\(n\\\\) est la taille de l\\'échantillon.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q2-expl', 'L\\'erreur standard est calculée comme suit : \\\\(\\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p})  \\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{0.60 \\\\times 0.40}{200}} = 0.03464102 \\\\approx 0.0346\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q2-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q2-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 3\n\n\nEn considérant le contexte de la question \\\\(1\\\\), vous souhaitez construire un intervalle de confiance pour \\\\(p\\\\) basé sur \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) à un niveau de confiance \\\\(\\\\alpha = 0.05\\\\). Quelle est la valeur du quantile que vous devez utiliser afin de construire cet intervalle de confiance?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_HMVKTLVIQR'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_HMVKTLVIQR\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(1.28\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_HMVKTLVIQR\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(1.645\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_HMVKTLVIQR\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(1.96\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_HMVKTLVIQR\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(2.58\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q3-hint', 'Pour un intervalle de confiance à \\\\(95\\\\%\\\\), on utilise le quantile de la distribution normale standard correspondant à \\\\(1 - \\\\frac{\\\\alpha}{2}\\\\).', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q3-expl', ' Ici, \\\\(\\\\alpha = 0.05\\\\), donc on cherche le quantile pour \\\\(1 - \\\\frac{0.05}{2} = 0.975\\\\). Le quantile pour un niveau de confiance de \\\\(95\\\\%\\\\) est ainsi \\\\(Z_{1-\\\\frac{\\\\alpha}{2}} = Z_{0.975} = 1.96\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q3-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q3-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 4\n\n\nEn utilisant le contexte des questions précédentes, calculez l'intervalle de confiance à \\\\(95\\\\%\\\\) pour la proportion \\\\(p\\\\) de personnes favorables au traité, en utilisant la proportion estimée \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) et l'erreur standard \\\\(\\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p})\\\\).\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_ABTIIFEAWQ'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ABTIIFEAWQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\([0.543,  0.657]\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ABTIIFEAWQ\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\([0.532,  0.668]\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ABTIIFEAWQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\([0.556,  0.644]\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ABTIIFEAWQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\([0.511,  0.689]\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q4-hint', 'Utilisez la formule de l\\'intervalle de confiance pour une proportion : \\\\(\\\\hat{p} \\\\pm Z_{1-\\\\frac{\\\\alpha}{2}} \\\\times \\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p})\\\\), où \\\\(Z_{1-\\\\frac{\\\\alpha}{2}}\\\\) est le quantile de la distribution normale standard correspondant au niveau de confiance souhaité.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q4-expl', 'L\\'intervalle de confiance à \\\\(95\\\\%\\\\) est calculé comme suit : \\\\(\\\\hat{p} \\\\pm 1.96 \\\\times \\\\text{e.s.}(\\\\hat{p}) = 0.60 \\\\pm 1.96 \\\\times 0.0346\\\\). Cela donne \\\\([0.532 0.668]\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q4-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q4-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 5\n\nConsidérons maintenant un niveau de confiance de 99% (c'est-à-dire \\\\(\\\\alpha=0.01\\\\)) au lieu de \\\\(95\\\\%\\\\). Quel sera l'effet sur la longueur de l'intervalle de confiance pour la proportion \\\\(p\\\\) de personnes favorables au traité ? La longueur de l'intervalle de confiance est donnée par la différence entre la borne supérieure et la borne inférieure de l'intervalle.\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_SVNIUAZORM'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_SVNIUAZORM\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>La longueur de l&apos;intervalle de confiance augmentera</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_SVNIUAZORM\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>La longueur de l&apos;intervalle de confiance diminuera</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_SVNIUAZORM\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>La longueur de l&apos;intervalle de confiance restera la même</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q5-hint', 'Revoyez comment calculer l\\'intervalle de confiance et l\\'impact sur la valeur du quantile considéré dans le calcul de l\\'intervalle de confiance lorsque \\\\(\\\\alpha\\\\) diminue.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q5-expl', 'Lorsque le niveau de confiance augmente, le quantile utilisé dans le calcul de l\\'intervalle de confiance augmente également. Cela entraîne ainsi une augmentation de la longueur de l\\'intervalle de confiance.', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q5-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q5-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 6\n\nVous souhaitez désormais tester l'hypothèse selon laquelle la proportion réelle de personnes favorables au traité est de \\\\(50\\\\%\\\\). Quelle est la formulation correcte des hypothèses statistique pour ce test ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_GUEYBFALUL'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_GUEYBFALUL\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(H_0: p = 0.60\\\\), \\\\(H_1: p ≠ 0.60\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_GUEYBFALUL\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(H_0: p = 0.50\\\\), \\\\(H_1: p ≠ 0.50\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_GUEYBFALUL\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(H_0: p = 0.50\\\\), \\\\(H_1: p > 0.60\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_GUEYBFALUL\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(H_0: p ≥ 0.50\\\\), \\\\(H_1: p < 0.50\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q6-hint', 'Rappelez-vous que l\\x27hypothèse nulle \\\\(H_0\\\\) correspond à l\\x27hypothèse de base, et l\\x27hypothèse alternative \\\\(H_1\\\\) est celle que vous cherchez à tester.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q6-expl', 'Nous cherchons à tester si la proportion diffère de \\\\(50\\\\%\\\\), donc \\\\(H_0: p = 0.50\\\\) et \\\\(H_1: p ≠ 0.50\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q6-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q6-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 7\n\nEn utilisant les hypothèses définies précédemment, calculez la statistique de test \\\\(z_{obs}\\\\). On rappelle que \\\\(\\\\hat{p} = 0.60\\\\), \\\\(n = 200\\\\), et \\\\(p_0 = 0.50\\\\).\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_RZVWUFDTTX'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_RZVWUFDTTX\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(Z \\\\approx 2.89\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_RZVWUFDTTX\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(Z \\\\approx 1.96\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_RZVWUFDTTX\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(Z \\\\approx 1.28\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_RZVWUFDTTX\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(Z \\\\approx 0.60\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q7-hint', 'Utilisez la formule du test : \\\\(Z = \\\\dfrac{\\\\hat{p} - p_0}{\\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{\\\\hat{p}(1-\\\\hat{p})}{n}}}\\\\)', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q7-expl', 'Avec \\\\(\\\\hat{p} = 0.60\\\\), \\\\(p_0 = 0.50\\\\), \\\\(n = 200\\\\), l\\x27erreur standard est environ 0.0346. Donc \\\\(z_{obs} = \\\\frac{0.60 - 0.50}{0.0346} \\\\approx 2.89\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q7-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q7-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 8\n\nÀ partir de la statistique de test calculée précédemment, déterminez la p-valeur associée au test (bilatéral).\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_NJBTXWYTMT'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NJBTXWYTMT\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.028\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NJBTXWYTMT\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0196\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NJBTXWYTMT\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0038\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NJBTXWYTMT\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.001\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-hint', 'Utilisez la formule : p-valeur = \\\\(2 \\\\times P(Z > |z_{obs}|)\\\\), avec \\\\(z_{obs} = 2.89\\\\), puis consultez  la table de la fonction cumulative de densité de la distribution standard normale.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-expl', 'La p-valeur se calcule comme \\\\(2 \\\\times P(Z > 2.89) \\\\approx 2 \\\\times 0.0019 = 0.0038\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 9\n\nQuelle est l'interprétation correcte d'une p-valeur de \\\\(0.0038\\\\) dans le contexte de ce test ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_JBYMCCHIZE'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBYMCCHIZE\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>Il y a une faible probabilité d&apos;observer une telle valeur de \\\\(\\\\hat{p}=0.60\\\\) si la vraie proportion était \\\\(0.50\\\\).</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBYMCCHIZE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>La proportion estimée est trop éloignée de \\\\(50\\\\%\\\\), donc \\\\(H_0\\\\) est forcément fausse.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBYMCCHIZE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>Cela signifie que \\\\(0.38\\\\%\\\\) des personnes interrogées sont favorables au traité.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBYMCCHIZE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>La probabilité que \\\\(H_0\\\\) soit vraie est de 0.0038.</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q9-hint', 'La p-valeur mesure la compatibilité entre les données observées et l\\x27hypothèse nulle.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q9-expl', 'Une p-valeur de \\\\(0.0038\\\\) signifie que, si \\\\(H_0\\\\) était vraie, il serait très rare (\\\\(0.38\\\\%\\\\)) d\\x27observer une telle distance entre \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) et \\\\(p_0\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q9-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q9-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 10\n\nÀ un niveau de signification \\\\(\\\\alpha = 0.05\\\\), que concluez-vous du test précédent ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_VKALSMZVSJ'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VKALSMZVSJ\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>On rejette \\\\(H_0\\\\) : il y a suffisamment de preuves pour conclure que la proportion réelle est différente de \\\\(50\\\\%\\\\).</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VKALSMZVSJ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>On accepte \\\\(H_0\\\\) : la proportion réelle est exactement de \\\\(50\\\\%\\\\).</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VKALSMZVSJ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>On ne rejette pas \\\\(H_0\\\\) : il n&apos;y a pas suffisamment de preuves.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_VKALSMZVSJ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>On ne peut pas conclure : l&apos;échantillon est trop petit.</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q10-hint', 'Comparez la p-valeur à \\\\(\\\\alpha = 0.05\\\\).', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q10-expl', 'Puisque la p-valeur est plus petite que 0.05, on rejette \\\\(H_0\\\\) au niveau de signification de \\\\(5\\\\%\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q10-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q10-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 11\n\nConsidérons maintenant un test unilatéral avec les hypothèses suivantes: \\\\(H_0: p=0.5\\\\) et \\\\(H_1: p<0.5\\\\).\nQuelle est la p-valeur associée?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_JHXPWGAHPK'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JHXPWGAHPK\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0001\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JHXPWGAHPK\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.9981\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JHXPWGAHPK\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.499\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"r